				\usepackage{amsbsy}
				\usepackage{mathrsfs}
				\usepackage{upgreek}
				\setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt}
				\begin{document}$M_{\mathrm{A}}$\end{document}MA) are able to penetrate further into the magnetosheath and impact the magnetopause more easily than under lower \documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
				\usepackage{amsmath}
				\usepackage{wasysym} 
				\usepackage{amsfonts} 
				\usepackage{amssymb} 
				\usepackage{amsbsy}
				\usepackage{mathrsfs}
				\usepackage{upgreek}
				\setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt}
				\begin{document}$M_{\mathrm{A}}$\end{document}MA conditions. However, jets may form also under these low \documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
