Plaschke et al. (2013) find typical recurrence times of a few minutes between two jet observations while a single spacecraft stays within the magnetosheath. However, the distribution of recurrence times is very broad and spans over three orders of magnitude, with inter-jet times ranging from 6 to \documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
				\usepackage{amsmath}
