				\begin{document}$S=S_{\mathrm{b}}$\end{document}S=Sb (the penetration distance). This prediction was tested and confirmed using the radially separated THEMIS spacecraft (Dubyagin et al. 2011) and by analyzing the conditions controlling particle injections to the geostationary orbit (Sergeev et al. 2012). Fig. 35
Illustrative sketch adapted from Sergeev et al. (2012). The color lines represent the entropy profile of the background plasma for different magnetotail configurations. Blue and red correspond to a quiet and stretched magnetotail, respectively. The plasma bubble continues to move earthward until its entropy (\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
