For isolated magnetic field structures with a clear decrease in field strength (‘negative structures’) Karlsson et al. (2016) concluded that these exist both in the pristine solar wind and in the magnetosheath (see Fig. 38), similar to Earth. Scale sizes and relative field decreases were also similar to the terrestrial diamagnetic plasmoids. Therefore, they are likely identical to ‘solar wind magnetic holes’ (e.g., Tsurutani et al. 2011) convected across the bow shock. Fig. 38
